destination1 = Destination.create(name: "Chicago", language: "Chicagoan", abbr: "CHI", description: "Chicago is the most populous city in the U.S. state of Illinois, and the third most populous city in the United States. With an estimated population of 2,693,976 in 2019, it is also the most populous city in the Midwestern United States. Located on the shores of freshwater Lake Michigan, Chicago Chicago is an international hub for finance, culture, commerce, industry, education, technology, telecommunications, and transportation.  Chicago's culture includes the visual arts, literature, film, theatre, comedy (especially improvisational comedy), food, and music, particularly jazz, blues, soul, hip-hop, gospel, and electronic dance music including house music. Chicago is famoulsy home of the NBA's Bulls and the MLB's Cubs.", highlights: "Millennium Park, Navy Pier, the Art Institue of Chicago, Sears Tower, Grant Park, the Musuem of Science And Industry, Wrigley Field")
Destination.create(name: "Paris", language: "French", abbr: "PAR", description: "Paris is the capital and most populous city of France, with an estimated population of 2,175,601 residents as of 2018, in an area of more than 41 square miles. Since the 17th century, Paris has been one of Europe's major centres of finance, diplomacy, commerce, fashion, science and arts. Paris is especially known for its museums and architectural landmarks: the Louvre was the most visited art museum in the world in 2019, with 9.6 million visitors. Paris was ranked as the second most visited travel destination in the world in 2019, is home to the Paris Saint-Germain Football Club and annually hosts the French Open, one of the four tennis grand slam tournaments.", highlights: "The Louvre, the Musée d'Orsay, the Musée des Arts et Métiers, The Arc de Triomphe, The Eiffel Tower, The Pantheon, Notre Dame, Palace of Versailles, Saint Denis Basillica")
Destination.create(name: "Madrid", language: "Spanish", abbr: "MAD", description: "Madrid is the capital and most-populous city of Spain with a population of almost 3.3 million and a metropolitan area population of approximately 6.5 million. Madrid is the second largest city in the European Union. Madrid's influence in politics, education, entertainment, environment, media, fashion, science, culture, and the arts all contribute to its status as one of the world's major global cities. Madrid is home to two world-famous football clubs, Real Madrid and Atlético Madrid. While Madrid possesses modern infrastructure, it has preserved the look and feel of many of its historic neighbourhoods and streets", highlights: "the Plaza Mayor, the Royal Palace of Madrid, the Royal Thatre, the Prado Museum, the Reina Sofia Museum, the Museum of Modern Art, Cibeles Palace and Fountain, the Santiago Bernabéu, the Metropolitano Stadium")
Destination.create(name: "Tokyo", language: "Japanese", abbr: "TYO", description: "Tokyo is the de facto capital and most populous prefecture of Japan. Located at the head of Tokyo Bay, the prefecture forms part of the Kanto Region on the central Pacific Coast of Japan's main island of Honshu. Tokyo is the political and economic center of the country, as well as the seat of the Emperor of Japan. As of 2021, the prefecture has an estimated population of 13,960,236. The Greater Tokyo Area is the most populous metropolitan area in the world with more than 37.3 million residents. Tokyo is the largest urban economy in the world by gross domestic product and is Japan's leading center of business and finance. Tokyo is an international center of research and development.", highlights: "University of Tokyo, the Imperial Palace, Shinjuku, Shibuya, the Shinkansen bullet train, the Ginza District, the National Museum of Nature and Science, the Senso-ji Temple, Ueno Park and Zoo, the Tokyo National Museum")
Destination.create(name: "Rome", language: "Italian", abbr: "ROM", description: "Rome is the capital city of Italy and is home to 2,860,009 resident's making it also the most populated comune in Italy. Located in the central-western portion of the Italian Peninsula, within Lazio, along the shore of the Tiber, Rome also houses the Vatican City within its borders. Rome is one of the most historically powerful and influential cities in the world, having been a major human settlement for almost three millennia. Filled with historic monuments, buildings, and site, Rome has long been a world cultural center, with the Renaissance, Baroque style, and Neoclassical style art being born here. For hundreds of years famous painters, artists, sculptors, and architects have made Rome their center of activity. Rome was also famously the seat of power of the Holy Roman Empire.", highlights: "The Vatican, The Pantheon, The Colosseum, St. Peter's Basilica, Trevi Fountain, the Roman Forum, the Catacombs, Villa Borgherem Palatine Hill,the Sistine Chapel, Piazza Navona, the Spanish Steps")
Destination.create(name: "Cairo", language: "Egyptian Arabic", abbr: "CAI", description: "Set on the banks of the Nile River, Cairo is the capital of and the largest city in Egypt, with a population of 9 million. The Cairo metropolitan area has a population of roughly 21.3 million, making it the most populated metropolitan area in Africa. Cairo is filled with history, being located within ancient Egypt, and famously boasts historic, ancient sites and cities including one of the seven wonders of the world: the Giza pyramids in the ancient city of Memphis. Cairo has long been the center of the region's political and cultural life and has the oldest and largest film and music industries in the Arab world.", highlights: "Tahir Square, Egyptian Museum, Tomb of King Tut, the Giza Pyramids, the Great Sphinx, Coptic Cairo, Cairo Citadel, Cairo Tower")
Destination.create(name: "Rio de Janeiro", language: "Portuguese", abbr: "RIO", description: "Rio de Janeiro is the second most populated city in Brazil with a population of 6.7 million. Commonly referred to as simply 'Rio', the city is headquarters to Brazil's oil, mining, and telecommunications industries. One of the most visited cities in the southern hemisphere, Rio is known for its beautiful natural settings and beaches. Rio also has one of the new seven wonders of the world: the giant statue of Christ the Redeemer atop Corcovado Mountain.", highlights: "Statue of Christ the Redeemer, Sugarloaf Mountain, the Sambodromo, Marcana Stadium, Carinal, samba, bossa, noba, and balneairo beaches")
Destination.create(name: "Kingston", language: "English", abbr: "KIN", description: "Kingston is the capital and largest city in Jamaica, located on the southeastern coast of the island. Two districts make up the central area of Kingstom: the historic Downtown and New Kingston. Kingston plays a central role in Jamaica's economy with the vast majority of economic activity taking place within Kingston as well as most government buildings being located within the City. The city is also home to the highest number of schools, hospital, and universities in Jamaica. On the beach and surrounded by the Blue Mountains, Red Hills, Long Mountain, and the Kingstom Harbor, Kingston offers beautiful surroundings and topography. ", highlights: "Beache, culture, native cuisine, the Bob Marley Museum, Devon House, Hope Botanical Gardens and Zoo, the Blue Mountains")
Destination.create(name: "Los Angeles", language: "English", abbr: "LAX", description: "Located on a broad basin in sunny Southern California, LA is the most populated city in California with a population of roughly four million, and is the second most populated city in the United States. Known for its Mediterranean climate, ethnic diversity, Hollywood entertainment industry, sprawling metropolis, and proximity to beautiful beaches, LA is an extremely popular tourist destination. LA is also infamously known for having terrible traffic, drivers beware. LA is home to some of the most historic and famous USA sports franchises including the NBA's Lakers and the MLB's Dodgers.", highlights: "Hollywood, Hollywood Sign, the Staples Center, Walt Disney Concert Hall, Disney Land, Venice Canals, Dodger Stadium, University of California Los Angeles, Hollywood Boulevard, Will Rogers State Historic Park")
Destination.create(name: "Berlin", language: "German", abbr: "BER", description: "Berlin is the capital and largest city of Germany by both area and population with a population of roughly 3.7 million. Berlin straddles the banks of the Spree River and is home to many lakes, with roughly 1/3rd of it's are composed of forests, parks, gardens, rivers, canals, and lakes. Berlin is a world city of culture, politics, media, and science, with its economy based on high-tech firms. Berlin is also home to world-renowned universities and contains three World Heritage Sites. ", highlights: "Museum Island, the Palaces and Parks of Potsdam and Berlin, the Berlin Museum, Bradenburg Gate, the Reichstag building, Potsdamer Platz, the Berlin Wall Memorial, the Old National Gallery, Bratwurst")
Destination.create(name: "Sydney", language: "English", abbr: "SYD", description: "Sydney is the capital city of the state of New South Wales and is the most populous city in Austrila with a population of 5,312,163. Located on Australia's east coast, the metropolis surrounds Port Jacskon and extends towards the Blue Mountains to the west. Sydney spans a huge area, containing 658 suburbs spread across 33 local governmental areas. There are at least 15 informal regions of Sydney. Sydney is considered one of the most expensive cities in the world but also one of the top ten most liveable ones. Syndey is widely considered as Australia's financial capital as it is home to a significant number of foreign banks and multinational corporations. Sydney is also home to the University of Sydney, a world leading university. Sydney also boasts over 2.5 million acres of nature reserves and parks.", highlights: "Sydney Opera House, Sydney Harbour, the Royal National Park, the Royal Botanic Garden, Hyde Park, Sydney Harbour Bridge, Central Station")


